## ğŸ§  What's Going On?

### 1. LLM Node

`llmCall(state)` - Routes the message to GPT-4o with system instructions to parse and execute or plan tool use.

### 2. ToolNode

Executes custom tools (`add`, `sub`, `multiply`, `div`) if the model calls them.

### 3. Conditional Routing

After each `llmCall`, we check:

- If tools are called â†’ go to tool execution
- Otherwise â†’ finish execution

---

## ğŸ“š LangChain vs LangGraph vs LangSmith

| Feature             | **LangChain**                                  | **LangGraph**                                        | **LangSmith**                                              |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ§  Purpose          | Build LLM-powered apps (chains, agents, tools) | Create dynamic, stateful LLM workflows as graphs     | Observability and debugging for LangChain pipelines        |
| âš™ï¸ Focus            | Chains, agents, tools, memory, retrievers      | State-based routing, conditionals, flow logic        | Logs, traces, evaluations, latency tracking                |
| ğŸ” Execution Model  | Linear or looping sequences (Chains)           | Directed graph of nodes with conditional edges       | Monitors and visualizes LangChain execution                |
| ğŸ‘· Used For         | Creating chains of LLM calls + logic           | Building agents that can reason, call tools, re-plan | Testing and improving agent performance                    |
| ğŸ” Observability    | Minimal                                        | Minimal                                              | Full logging, tracing, and evaluations                     |
| ğŸ§© Tool Integration | Built-in tool abstraction and binding          | Compatible (via `ToolNode`)                          | Tracks tool calls and outcomes                             |
| ğŸ§ª Dev Experience   | Easy to prototype with chains                  | Ideal for advanced agents or dynamic workflows       | Ideal for improving models and debugging production issues |

